translated: Johansson, Sven Reinhold, regimental veterinarian, Eksjö, b. July 16, 1895 in Eksjö to J. A. J. and Emma Gustafsson. Married Viola Andersson in 1927. Children: UHa b. 1928, Kerstin b. 1930, Margit b. 1935. Completed his studies in Växjö in 1914, veterinarian degree in 1916, and veterinary examination in 1918. Assistant at the veterinary college from 1919 to 1920, battalion veterinarian in the BVK reserve from 1920, in Karlsborg's garrison in 1921, in Små’L's Husireg. in 1922, in Göta Ingkår in 1928, captain's position in 1930, regimental veterinarian in the FVK since 1935, major's position since 1940. Participated in tactical winter training for military veterinarians in 1927, served in the army administration medical service in 1930, and participated in tactical training courses in meat inspection for battalion veterinarians in 1934. Scientific assistant at the state veterinary bacterial institute in 1920 and meat inspection official at the Karlsborg storage depot from 1921 to 1922. Head of the Eksjö meat inspection office since 1922 and city veterinarian in Eksjö since 1922. Member of the city council from 1931 to 1934 and chairman of the health committee since 1927. Awarded RVO.
